LAGOS â€“ The Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC) Lagos State Sector Command has reiterated its commitment to strategic road safety partnership for innovative intervention in eradicating road traffic crashes and the creation of a safe monitoring environment for Nigerians. CC Olusegun Ogungbemide, the Lagos Sector Commander of Corps, disclosed this while receiving Brig. Gen. ASM Wase, Commander 9 Brigade Nigerian Army in his office during a working visit to RS2.1 Lagos Sector Command, Ojodu on Tuesday. While appreciating the Commander for the visit and for sustaining the existing collaboration between the two agencies, the Sector Commander harped on the need that visits like this will foster the existing relationship and improve public enlightenment, promotion of stakeholders cooperation, robust data management, prompt rescue services and effective patrol operation. Lagos Begins Publication Of Sex Offenders FRSC Records 756 Road Accidents In Kaduna In his remark, the Commander 9 Brigade Brig. Gen. ASM Wase noted that the visit is to familiarize with sister agencies in Lagos State, especially the Federal Safety Corps to maintain the cordial relationships for improved partnership towards effective and efficient operations aimed at ensuring safety of lives and properties in the State. The Sector Commander also used the opportunity to take the Commander to the Drivers Licence Center for facility tour of the Command. The Commander also visited the Zonal Commanding Officer RS2Lagos in charge of Lagos and Ogun State, Assistant Corps Marshal Peter Kibo.